It displays various network related information such as network connections, routing tables, interface.

$ netstat
$ netstat -a                            (To list all ports and connections)
$ netstat -at                           (To list all TCP ports)
$ netstat -au                           (To list all UDP ports)
$ netstat -l                            (To list only listening ports)
$ netstat -lt                           (To list all listening TCP ports)
$ netstat -lu                           (To list all listening UDP ports)
$ netstat -lx                           (To list all listening UNIX ports) 
$ netstat -i                            (To list of network interface)
$ netstat -r                            (Kernel IP Routing Table)
$ netstat -pt                           (To display the PID)
$ netstat -an | grep ':PORT_NO'         (Particular Port)
EG: netstat -an | grep ':80'
$ netstat -ap | grep SERVICE_NAME       (Particular Service)
EG: netstat -ap | grep ssh
